Charming and thoughtful spin on The Game of Life formula, and a worthy alternative to any Sims game. A rare vestige from the game design age when you could pay for a finished product and enjoy it to its utmost, versus the predatory microtransactions and limited time crossovers of everything else clogging up the Play Store these days. What little this game lacks in shallow, iOS-style polish, it more than makes up for by being a cute, intelligent, COMPLETE experience.
